<TITLE> Tuku's wife back home on bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 8 (bdnews24.com) -- Former state minister for power Iqbal Hasan Mahmud Tuku's wife Romana Mahmud who was arrested in a corruption case was freed on bail Monday, a top prisons official said. Deputy inspector general (prisons) Major Shamsul Haider Siddiqui told bdnews24.com: "Romana Mahmud was released from jail Monday afternoon. Her daughter Sarah Hasin Mahmud was released on bail last week." Both received bails from the High Court, Ashfaque, an official for Tuku's business firm, told bdnews24.com. Police arrested Romana Mahmud and her daughter at their Mohammadpur home on July 3 in the corruption case filed with Mohammadpur Police Station. Tuku's son Abed Hasan Mahmud, accused in the same case, surrendered to the trial court the same day. Joint forces arrested Iqbal Mahmud Tuku on Feb 3. He is still in jail. bdnew
